SIMPLE: sober
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sober
<hw>Sober</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Soberer</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Soberest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>sobre</ets>, F.
<ets>sobre</ets>, from L. <ets>sobrius</ets>, probably from a prefix
<ets>so-</ets> expressing separation + <ets>ebrius</ets> drunken. Cf.
<er>Ebriety</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Temperate in the use of
spirituous liquors; habitually temperate; <as>as, a <ex>sober</ex>
man</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That we may hereafter live a godly, righteous, and
<qex>sober</qex> life, to the glory of Thy holy name.</q> <rj><qau>Bk.
of Com. Prayer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not intoxicated or excited by spirituous liquors;
<as>as, the sot may at times be <ex>sober</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not mad or insane; not wild, visionary, or heated
with passion; exercising cool, dispassionate reason; self-controlled;
self-possessed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There was not a <qex>sober</qex> person to be had; all was
tempestuous and blustering.</q> <rj><au>Druden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No <qex>sober</qex> man would put himself into danger for the
applause of escaping without breaking his neck.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1365 --></p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Not proceeding from, or attended with, passion;
calm; <as>as, <ex>sober</ex> judgment; a man in his <ex>sober</ex>
senses.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Serious or subdued in demeanor, habit, appearance,
or color; solemn; grave; sedate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What parts gay France from <qex>sober</qex> Spain?</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>See her <qex>sober</qex> over a sampler, or gay over a jointed
baby.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Twilight gray⟦br⟧
Had in her <qex>sober</qex> livery all things clad.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Grave; temperate; abstinent; abstemious;
moderate; regular; steady; calm; quiet; cool; collected; dispassionate;
unimpassioned; sedate; staid; serious; solemn; somber. See
<er>Grave</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sober</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sober
<hw>So"ber</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Sobered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sobering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make sober.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There shallow draughts intoxicate the brain,⟦br⟧
And drinking largely <qex>sobers</qex> us again.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sober</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sober
<hw>So"ber</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become sober; -- often with
<xex>down</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Vance gradually <qex>sobered</qex> down.</q> <rj><qau>Ld.
Lytton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soberize</ent>⟦br⟧
